## Best Practices Summary

### Window Functions
1. Always specify PARTITION BY and ORDER BY explicitly
2. Use ROWS BETWEEN for running calculations
3. Test window logic on small dataset first
4. Consider performance impact (use tables for complex windows)

### Sessionization
1. Document timeout rule clearly (30 minutes)
2. Handle first interaction (NULL time gap)
3. Generate deterministic session IDs
4. Create debug models for verification

### Deduplication
1. Use ROW_NUMBER() not DISTINCT
2. Order by meaningful column (updated_at)
3. Add metadata (was_duplicate flag)
4. Document deduplication logic

### Materialization
1. Default to views (easy to change)
2. Use tables for: complex queries, frequently accessed, large datasets
3. Avoid ephemeral unless single downstream use
4. Monitor build times

